thisinformation he can ponder the fact that while the government does nottap every conversation that they have a record of tapping many conversationsthat they have no right to, even under their own laws. Given the longhistory of members of the US government ignoring the laws that applyto them, it is no wonder that so many people in here sound so paranoid, andgiven the fact that it is often difficult or impossible to punish theseindividuals once they are discovered, it is no wonder that so many peoplein here have so little faith in the escrow proposal for Clipper.Jamie Jamison
