easy tounderstand. The whole rest of your article is based on a large seriesof false premises, all predicated on the notion that this simple actis somehow impossible.I feel free to presume to tell you that you do not seem to understandthe mechanics of the proposal. Arguing that terrorists will be killingpeople for their clipper phones is silly because its pointless. Letsbe alarmist about what really would show up as a problem, shall we?--Perry Metzgerpmetzger@shearson.com--Laissez faire, laissez passer. Le monde va de lui meme.
