ns for one hour each, plus the cost of a laptop finally blown to pieces in a spectacular, Hollywood-like bonfire; add travelling expenses, drinks and lighting, divide the sum by 300) there won't be a larger demand -- not from the private sector anyway. And let me mention one other thought that certainly has occurred to all the notoriously paranoid people in this group before: Who is going to verify that _no_ interested party will perform tempest attacks on the vault?? Where there's so much smoke and mirrors -- there can't be a nice, honest fire but something really worth hiding ... --Detlef Lannert       DC3EK       E-Mail: tsos@rz.uni-duesseldorf.dePGP 2.2 key via server or finger lannert@clio.rz.uni-duesseldorf.de"I am Psmith." - "Oh, you're Smith, are you?" - "With a preliminaryP. Which, however, is not sounded."                   P.G.Wodehouse
